5|$|In September 2000, the Louvre Museum {{dedicated}} the Gilbert Chagoury and Rose-Marie Chagoury Gallery {{to display}} tapestries {{donated by the}} Chagourys, including a 16th-century six-part tapestry suite, sewn with gold and silver threads representing sea divinities, which was commissioned in Paris for Colbert de Seignelay, <b>Secretary</b> <b>of</b> <b>State</b> <b>for</b> the Navy.|$|E
